Handle escalated customer complaints and resolve issues promptly.
Ensure compliance with manufacturer standards and company policies.
Collaborate with sales and marketing teams to drive customer retention.
Manage budgets, expenses, and resource allocation for the aftersales department.
Conduct regular training and development for aftersales staff.
Identify opportunities for process improvement and operational efficiency.
